The detailed analysis imbibes the thermodynamic and heat transfer aspects of a solar collector system. The thermal performance of a solar collector facing the true south is investigated based on the law of entropy. The mass flow across the solar collector area is assumed to be constant, so the fluid is considered to be incompressible, steady, with no change in its hydrodynamic properties with temperature, and there is no increase in energy of the system ∂E∂τ=0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
