				\begin{document}$$ \frac{\partial E}{\partial \tau }=0 $$\end{document}. The air is used as a carrier fluid, and the change in enthalpy is calculated by using the steady flow energy equation (SFEE). The exergy function is calculated at the inlet and outlet of the solar collector. The inlet and outlet ports are assumed to be the same in the cross-section, so the loss due to the pipe bending, sudden enlargement and sudden contraction are absent in the calculation. The rate of change in entropy of the collector plate is assumed to be zero ∂s∂τ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
